text.tspan: Each battery stack connected by a separate diode protected charge and discharge bus.
The internal battery management system disconnects disharging it the batteries are too
low and disconnects charging when any battery has been charged to capacity
PV panels are connected in parallel through EIQ VBoost
DC-DC converters which connect in parallel which operate as
charge controllers to the DC Bus
DC BUSWAY (Universal Electric) 260 to 420 VDC depending on charge source
There are three sources of DC power to the
BUSWAY. The grid-connected charger, the battery
stacks (4) and the three EIQ DC-DC converter PV
arrays. The charger and all battery stacks have
them to the bus. The EIQ only provides power to
the bus when there is a voltage present on the
bus. A separate DC loop is connected to power
the contactors. When disconneted , all power to
the BUSWAY drops to zero within 10 ms.
BUSWAY IS LOOSELY GROUNDED THRU TWO
SMALL RESISTORS TO A CENTER EARTH GROUND.
THE VOLTAGE ON THESE TWO RESISTORS IS
MEASURED TO DETERMINE A GROUND FAULT
